Next Release [V2.4]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
Fixed: Headshot action on team-kills for the game "Counter-Strike"
- Syntax adapated for 1.8.3
- Minor changes
- Compiled against 1.8.3-dev+5116


29. May 2013 [V2.3]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
+ Reworked weapon stats handling. Other plugins are now working properly beside
  gameME Stats, for example the "/me" command
- Minor changes


23. February 2013 [V2.2]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
+ Added "Reset Statistics" to player menu (gameME menu)
Fixed: Crashes because of players without team-id
- Minor changes


31. March 2012 [V2.1]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
+ Added dynamic support to block ingame commands
+ Added support for Half-Life: Deathmatch
- Minor changes


02. February 2010 [V2.0]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
+ Plugin is now called "gameME Plugin"
+ Multiple recipients for ingame messages
+ Major performance improvements


09. September 2009 [V1.9]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
- Internal Release


02. August 2008 [V1.8]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
- Adapted ingame menu for the game "Team Fortress Classic"


02. August 2008 [V1.7]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
+ Removed default message prefix and introduce a new cvar to define the prefix manually
- Removed some unncessary stuff
- Make the code more stable and reliable
Fixed: Some debug messages


08. July 2008 [V1.6]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
+ Extend logging with locations for kill and suicides
- Refactoring
- Minor changes
Fixed: Bots are not swapped on the "hlx_amx_swap" command
Fixed: Several bugs for "Natural Selection"


30. June 2008 [V1.5]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
+ Major performance improvements
+ Added "hlx_amx_hint" command
+ Added TeamInfo event to ensure the correct team colors (cstrike only)
+ Added support for the game "Team Fortress Classic"
+ Added support for the game "Natural Selection"
- Reworked "hlx_amx_csay" command
Fixed: "hlx_amx_say" command not working


9. December 2007 [V1.4]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
+ Trigger player action "headshot" on headshot kill
- Team colors are checked on every call


2. December 2007 [V1.3]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
+ Added HLstatsX Ingame Menu triggered by "hlx", "hlstatsx", "hlx_menu"
+ Added colored chat messages for the game cstrike
+ Block HLstatsX ingame commands by default from the chat area
+ Added "hlx_amx_psay2" command to display complete messages in green (cstrike only)
+ Added swap command to enable Team-Balancer support
+ Added public cvars for the ingame plugin
Fixed: Some minor bugs and removed unnecessary code
Fixed: The webpages in the motd are now scrollable


8. November 2007 [V1.2]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
Fixed: Too high stack memory allocation
Fixed: Plugin recompile for latest amxx version 1.8

